</nav></header><main aria-label="main content"><div class="speakable">
      <b data-is-speakable>Cooking During COVID-19: Family Meals And Fantasies Of Future Dinner Parties</b>   <b data-is-speakable>Food writer Sam Sifton says the resurgence of family meals is one of the "precious few good things" to come of the pandemic. He says his family is eating a lot of tinned fish and cabbage these days.</b>
</div>
